# 07 — Firmware Standard

## Layering (mandatory separation)

HAL · drivers · platform services · domain logic · configuration · communication · diagnostics · application

No peripheral register access from domain logic.

## Ownership

Each service: responsibility, public interface, dependencies, state, error behavior, test strategy. Minimize global mutable state.

## Determinism (safety-relevant paths)

No unbounded loops · no blocking in real-time paths · no uncontrolled dynamic allocation · no silent error suppression.

## Watchdog

Service reflects health of critical services — not generic timer kick alone.

## Protocol serialization

Never send raw compiler-dependent structs on CAN, SPI, UART, or network.

Use `firmware/shared/` layouts: explicit sizes, endianness, scaling, version, CRC.

## Configuration

Vehicle behavior in `config/vehicles/*.yaml` → binary via `tools/config_compiler`. No E30 hardcoding in common code.

## Layout

`firmware/shared`, `firmware/dcc/logic`, `firmware/dcc/radio` per `agents_stuff/CODE_LAYOUT_PLAN.md`.

Imports at top of file (no inline imports unless documented circular dependency).

Do not write firmware in foundation/documentation work packages unless explicitly tasked.
